          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Hostage list approved</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-jan-8-2.jpg" alt="Hostage list approved" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Israel and Hamas continue <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-08-01-2025-h2-3-indirect-negotiations" target="_blank">indirect negotiations</a> for a ceasefire and hostage exchange, with Hamas reportedly approving a list of 34 Israeli hostages. However, Israel denies receiving the list and awaits confirmation of the hostages' status. Talks in Doha, mediated by international officials, have seen limited progress. Meanwhile, <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-08-01-2025-h2-4-israeli-airstrikes-continue" target="_blank">Israeli airstrikes continue</a> as Gaza's health ministry reports over 45,000 deaths and 109,000 injuries since October 2023 as hospitals struggle to cope with the surge in casualties.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">The conflict's humanitarian toll remains dire. International mediators, including US officials and regional powers like Egypt, aim to finalize a ceasefire agreement, but the goal of finding a resolution keeps coming short. A released video of one of the hostages has prompted even more <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-08-01-2025-h2-5-israeli-to-take-to-the-streets" target="_blank">Israelis to take to the streets</a> to demand a hostage-ceasefire deal from the Israeli government.</p>
        </mj-text>
