          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">Macron‚Äôs Ukrainian expectations</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">French President Emmanuel Macron restated France's role as <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-08-01-2025-h3-6-strong-ally-to-donald-trump" target="_blank">a strong ally to Donald Trump</a> while urging Europe to strengthen its unity and resilience. Macron calls for realistic discussions on Ukraine's war. However, he also warns against a rushed settlement to end the war. Calling for Ukraine to be more realistic about the war and territory has become a more popular consensus, even among countries in the West that support Ukraine.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">To mitigate some of this war fatigue, Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky appeared on <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-08-01-2025-h3-7-lex-fridman-poscast" target="_blank">Lex Fridman's podcast</a> to counter narratives sympathetic to Russia and address US aid concerns. He stated that peace requires Russian accountability and defended Ukraine's anti-corruption efforts. Zelensky warns against the risks of potential naive peace negotiations without security guarantees.
</p>
