          <h2 style="font-size:20px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500; margin-top:2px !important">Why did Argentina decline BRICS membership?</h2>
        </mj-text>
         <mj-image padding="10px 12px" width="600px" src="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com/email/images/gp-jan-8-3.jpg" alt="Why did Argentina decline BRICS membership?" href="https://www.geopoliticalsummary.com" />
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">In December 2023, Argentina's newly elected President, Javier Milei, announced that the country <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-08-01-2025-f1-10-would-not-join-the-brics" target="_blank">would not join the BRICS</a> bloc. This reversed the previous administration under Former President Alberto Fernandez‚Äôs decision to <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-08-01-2025-f2-11-apply-for-membership" target="_blank">apply for membership</a> and its subsequent invitation to join the bloc. The decision not to join BRICS came after Milei's surprise election victory in November 2023. Argentina was set to join the BRICS on January 1, 2024, with five other members. 
</p>
           <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Javier Milei is a right-wing populist. His biggest qualm with the bloc was <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-08-01-2025-f3-12-china-economic-dominance" target="_blank">China's economic dominance</a>. They had control of 70% of the bloc‚Äôs GDP before the expansion and still hold more than the other members put together. He said Argentina would not become a full member but aimed to strengthen trade and investment ties. This policy shift resulted from his broader economic and political reforms, which included tackling inflation and economic instability. 
</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">Argentina had a serious problem with inflation before the 2023 election; the annual inflation rate was 160%, and the poverty rate was 49% of the population. Their currency was devalued, and these factors were attributed to his win. In addition, <a href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-08-01-2025-f4-13-his-views-on-foreign-policy" target="_blank">his views on foreign policy</a> differ significantly from those of the previous government. Milei also wanted a foreign policy that favored the United States and did not contradict ‚ÄúWestern values.‚Äù
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
